25|$|On February 26, 2000, <b>De</b> <b>La</b> <b>Hoya</b> {{knocked out}} Derrell Coley (34–1–2) in a WBC eliminator. The WBC awarded <b>De</b> <b>La</b> <b>Hoya</b> their welterweight title, which he lost, to Shane Mosley (34–0) by a split {{decision}} on 17 June 2000, giving <b>De</b> <b>La</b> <b>Hoya</b> the first sound defeat of his pro career. The fight was a disputed decision, with one judge scoring the fight 115–113 for <b>De</b> <b>La</b> <b>Hoya,</b> {{and the other}} two scoring it 116–112 and 115–113 for Mosley.|$|E
