25|$|On June 7, 1996, Oscar <b>De</b> <b>La</b> <b>Hoya</b> fought Mexican legend Julio César Chávez (96–1–1) for the lineal and WBC light welterweight championship. <b>De</b> <b>la</b> <b>Hoya,</b> with {{a record}} of 21–0 with 19 K.Os, {{defeated}} Chavez by a fourth-round TKO. The fight was stopped due to a bad cut suffered by Chavez. Until their rematch in 1998, Chávez stated that <b>De</b> <b>La</b> <b>Hoya</b> did not defeat him since the fight was stopped. <b>De</b> <b>La</b> <b>Hoya</b> successfully defended his titles with a twelve-round unanimous decision against undefeated former WBC Lightweight Champion and number one light welterweight contender Miguel Ángel González (41–0–0).|$|E
